## mlld-run code block examples

```mlld-run
@text executable = "This is executable code!"
@data settings = {"mode": "production"}
@run [echo "Processing in {{settings.mode}} mode"]
@add @executable
```

```mlld-run
@import { helper } from "./utils.mld"
@path output = "./results.txt"
@text result = [[Generated at {{TIME}}]]
@output @result to @output
```

## Mixed markdown with mlld-run

This is regular markdown text that should not be highlighted as mlld.

```mlld-run
@text warning = "⚠️ This code will execute!"
@when @settings.mode === "production" => @add @warning
```

More markdown content here.

```mlld
@text docs = "This is documentation only - will not execute"
@run [echo "This is just documentation"]
```